---

## Key Features for a Good Site Chatbot

1. **Rich Context** - The bot needs to know your programs, mission, FAQs, application process, etc.
2. **Streaming responses** - You have this âœ“
3. **Conversation memory** - Maintain context across messages
4. **Guardrails** - Keep it on-topic, prevent hallucinations about your programs
5. **Source citations** - "Learn more at /donate" type references
6. **Fallback to human** - "Contact us at..." for complex questions

---

## Best Approach: RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)

For a content-heavy site, you want **RAG** - the bot retrieves relevant context before answering.

### Option A: Simple (Good for small sites) - Static Context Injection

Create a knowledge base file that gets injected into the system prompt:

```typescript
// lib/chatbot-context.ts
export const HIIIWAV_CONTEXT = `
# About HiiiWAV
HiiiWAV is a creative tech incubator empowering artists to become successful entrepreneurs.

## Programs

### AFRO AI Accelerator
- 12-week program for artists building AI-powered music tech startups
- Up to $120k in funding
- Mentorship from industry experts
- Application deadline: [DATE]
- Apply at: hiiiwav.org/apply

### Events
- Monthly community meetups
- Annual showcase

## FAQs
Q: Who can apply to AFRO AI?
A: Artists and musicians building technology products in the music space.

Q: How do I donate?
A: Visit hiiiwav.org/donate

## Contact
- Email: hello@hiiiwav.org
- Instagram: @hiiiwav
`;
```

Then update your route:

```typescript
// app/api/ai/chat/route.ts
import { openai } from '@ai-sdk/openai'
import { streamText } from 'ai'
import { HIIIWAV_CONTEXT } from '@/lib/chatbot-context'

export const runtime = 'edge'

export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const { messages } = await req.json()
  
  const result = streamText({
    model: openai('gpt-4o-mini'), // cheaper, faster, good enough for FAQ
    messages,
    system: `You are the HiiiWAV assistant. Answer questions about HiiiWAV programs, 
events, and how to get involved. Be concise and helpful.

IMPORTANT RULES:
- Only answer questions related to HiiiWAV
- If you don't know something, say so and suggest contacting hello@hiiiwav.org
- Always include relevant links when mentioning pages
- Never make up program details, dates, or funding amounts

KNOWLEDGE BASE:
${HIIIWAV_CONTEXT}`,
    temperature: 0.3, // lower = more factual, less creative
    maxTokens: 500,
  })
  
  return result.toTextStreamResponse()
}
```

### Option B: Dynamic RAG (Better for larger sites with blog posts)

Use embeddings to search your content:

1. **Embed your content** - Store page content + blog posts as vectors
2. **On each query** - Find the 3-5 most relevant chunks
3. **Inject into prompt** - Send only relevant context

Tools for this:
- **Vercel AI SDK + Postgres pgvector** (you already have Neon/Postgres)
- **Pinecone** or **Supabase Vector** for managed vector DB

## UI Component

You'll want a chat widget. Here's a simple one using your existing `@ai-sdk/react`:

```tsx
// components/chat-widget.tsx
'use client'

import { useChat } from '@ai-sdk/react'
import { useState } from 'react'
import { MessageCircle, X, Send } from 'lucide-react'

export function ChatWidget() {
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false)
  const { messages, input, handleInputChange, handleSubmit, isLoading } = useChat({
    api: '/api/ai/chat',
  })

  return (
    <>
      {/* Toggle Button */}
      <button
        onClick={() => setOpen(!open)}
        className="fixed bottom-6 right-6 z-50 bg-[#00ff00] text-black p-4 rounded-full shadow-lg hover:scale-110 transition"
      >
        {open ? <X size={24} /> : <MessageCircle size={24} />}
      </button>

      {/* Chat Window */}
      {open && (
        <div className="fixed bottom-24 right-6 z-50 w-80 h-96 bg-black border border-[#00ff00]/30 rounded-lg flex flex-col shadow-2xl">
          <div className="p-3 border-b border-[#00ff00]/30">
            <h3 className="text-[#00ff00] font-bold">HiiiWAV Assistant</h3>
          </div>
          
          <div className="flex-1 overflow-y-auto p-3 space-y-3">
            {messages.length === 0 && (
              <p className="text-gray-500 text-sm">Ask me about HiiiWAV programs!</p>
            )}
            {messages.map((m) => (
              <div
                key={m.id}
                className={`text-sm ${m.role === 'user' ? 'text-white text-right' : 'text-gray-300'}`}
              >
                {m.content}
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>

          <form onSubmit={handleSubmit} className="p-3 border-t border-[#00ff00]/30 flex gap-2">
            <input
              value={input}
              onChange={handleInputChange}
              placeholder="Ask a question..."
              className="flex-1 bg-gray-900 text-white text-sm px-3 py-2 rounded border border-gray-700 focus:border-[#00ff00] outline-none"
            />
            <button
              type="submit"
              disabled={isLoading}
              className="bg-[#00ff00] text-black p-2 rounded disabled:opacity-50"
            >
              <Send size={16} />
            </button>
          </form>
        </div>
      )}
    </>
  )
}
```

Add to your layout:

```tsx
// app/layout.tsx
import { ChatWidget } from '@/components/chat-widget'

// In your body:
<ChatWidget />
```

## My Recommendation

Given your site size:

1. **Start with Option A** (static context) - quick to implement, good enough for now
2. **Write a comprehensive `chatbot-context.ts`** with all program details, FAQs, links
3. **Use `gpt-4o-mini`** - 10x cheaper than gpt-4o, fast, good for FAQ-style
4. **Add the chat widget** to the bottom-right corner
5. **Track questions** - Log what users ask to improve the knowledge base over time

Later, if you have 50+ blog posts and need semantic search, upgrade to RAG with pgvector.

## 2. Update the chat API route

```typescript:app/api/ai/chat/route.ts
import { openai } from '@ai-sdk/openai'
import { streamText } from 'ai'
import { HIIIWAV_CONTEXT } from '@/lib/chatbot-context'

export const runtime = 'edge'

export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const { messages } = await req.json()
  
  const result = streamText({
    model: openai('gpt-4o-mini'), // Cheaper and faster, good for FAQ-style responses
    messages,
    system: `You are the HiiiWAV assistant, a helpful and friendly chatbot for hiiiwav.org. 
Your role is to answer questions about HiiiWAV programs, events, how to get involved, and general information.

IMPORTANT RULES:
- Only answer questions related to HiiiWAV, its programs, events, or how to get involved
- If asked about something not related to HiiiWAV, politely redirect: "I'm here to help with questions about HiiiWAV. How can I assist you?"
- If you don't know specific information (like exact dates, application deadlines, etc.), say so and suggest contacting hello@hiiiwav.org
- Always include relevant links when mentioning pages (e.g., "Learn more at hiiiwav.org/donate")
- Never make up program details, dates, funding amounts, or other specific information
- Be concise and friendly - aim for 2-3 sentences unless more detail is requested
- Use the knowledge base below to answer questions accurately

KNOWLEDGE BASE:
${HIIIWAV_CONTEXT}`,
    temperature: 0.3, // Lower temperature = more factual, less creative
    maxTokens: 500, // Keep responses concise
  })
  
  return result.toTextStreamResponse()
}
```

## 3. Update the chat widget component

```typescript:components/ai/chat-widget.tsx
'use client'

import { useChat } from '@ai-sdk/react'
import { useState } from 'react'
import { MessageCircle, X, Send } from 'lucide-react'
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'
import { Input } from '@/components/ui/input'

export function ChatWidget() {
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false)
  const { messages, input, handleInputChange, handleSubmit, isLoading } = useChat({
    api: '/api/ai/chat',
  })

  return (
    <>
      {/* Toggle Button */}
      <button
        onClick={() => setOpen(!open)}
        className="fixed bottom-6 right-6 z-50 bg-[#00ff00] text-black p-4 rounded-full shadow-lg hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-200 hover:bg-[#00cc00]"
        aria-label="Open chat"
      >
        {open ? <X size={24} /> : <MessageCircle size={24} />}
      </button>

      {/* Chat Window */}
      {open && (
        <div className="fixed bottom-24 right-6 z-50 w-96 h-[600px] bg-black border-2 border-[#00ff00]/30 rounded-lg flex flex-col shadow-2xl">
          {/* Header */}
          <div className="p-4 border-b border-[#00ff00]/30 flex justify-between items-center">
            <div>
              <h3 className="text-[#00ff00] font-bold text-lg">HiiiWAV Assistant</h3>
              <p className="text-gray-400 text-xs">Ask me about our programs!</p>
            </div>
            <button
              onClick={() => setOpen(false)}
              className="text-gray-400 hover:text-white transition-colors"
              aria-label="Close chat"
            >
              <X size={20} />
            </button>
          </div>
          
          {/* Messages */}
          <div className="flex-1 overflow-y-auto p-4 space-y-4">
            {messages.length === 0 && (
              <div className="text-center text-gray-500 text-sm space-y-2">
                <p className="font-semibold text-[#00ff00]">Welcome! ðŸ‘‹</p>
                <p>Ask me about:</p>
                <ul className="list-disc list-inside text-left space-y-1 text-xs">
                  <li>AFRO AI accelerator program</li>
                  <li>How to donate</li>
                  <li>Upcoming events</li>
                  <li>Getting involved</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            )}
            {messages.map((m) => (
              <div
                key={m.id}
                className={`flex ${m.role === 'user' ? 'justify-end' : 'justify-start'}`}
              >
                <div
                  className={`max-w-[80%] rounded-lg px-4 py-2 ${
                    m.role === 'user'
                      ? 'bg-[#00ff00] text-black'
                      : 'bg-gray-900 border border-[#00ff00]/20 text-gray-100'
                  }`}
                >
                  <div className="text-sm whitespace-pre-wrap break-words">
                    {m.content}
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
            {isLoading && (
              <div className="flex justify-start">
                <div className="bg-gray-900 border border-[#00ff00]/20 rounded-lg px-4 py-2">
                  <div className="flex gap-1">
                    <div className="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-[#00ff00] animate-bounce" />
                    <div className="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-[#00ff00] animate-bounce [animation-delay:0.2s]" />
                    <div className="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-[#00ff00] animate-bounce [animation-delay:0.4s]" />
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            )}
          </div>

          {/* Input Form */}
          <form onSubmit={handleSubmit} className="p-4 border-t border-[#00ff00]/30 flex gap-2">
            <Input
              value={input}
              onChange={handleInputChange}
              placeholder="Ask a question..."
              className="flex-1 bg-gray-900 text-white border-gray-700 focus:border-[#00ff00] focus:ring-[#00ff00]"
              disabled={isLoading}
            />
            <Button
              type="submit"
              disabled={isLoading || !input.trim()}
              className="bg-[#00ff00] text-black hover:bg-[#00cc00] disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed"
            >
              <Send size={16} />
            </Button>
          </form>
        </div>
      )}
    </>
  )
}
```

Several options to grab media from the Elementor site:

## Option 1: Browser DevTools (Easiest)

1. Open **hiiiwav.org** in Chrome
2. Right-click â†’ **Inspect** â†’ **Network** tab
3. Filter by **Media** or **Img**
4. Refresh the page - all loaded videos/images will appear
5. Right-click each â†’ **Open in new tab** â†’ Save

For videos specifically, look for `.mp4`, `.webm` files in the Network tab.

## Option 2: WordPress Media Library Direct Access

If you have WP admin access:
1. Go to `hiiiwav.org/wp-admin/upload.php`
2. Select all media â†’ **Bulk actions** â†’ **Download** (if available)
3. Or use a plugin like **"Export Media Library"** to download as ZIP

## Option 3: Let Me Scrape the URLs

I can look at the live site and find the video/image URLs directly:

```bash
# Example - grab all media URLs from homepage
curl -s https://hiiiwav.org | grep -oE 'https://hiiiwav.org/wp-content/uploads/[^"]+\.(mp4|webm|jpg|png|gif|webp)'
```

## Option 4: View Page Source

1. Go to hiiiwav.org
2. **View Source** (Ctrl+U / Cmd+U)
3. Search for `wp-content/uploads` to find all media URLs
4. Videos are often in `<video>` tags or as background in `data-` attributes

+ # Marketing &amp; Analytics Agent
+ 
+ ## Your Role
+ You are responsible for Meta Pixel integration, UTM tracking, landing page optimization, and ad campaign support.
+ 
+ ## Key Context
+ - **$40k Meta ad credits** to spend in ~30 days
+ - Need clear, trackable landing pages for each initiative
+ - Fast iteration on copy and creative (AI-assisted, human-approved)
+ 
+ ## Key Files
+ - &#96;/app/layout.tsx&#96; - For Pixel installation
+ - &#96;/lib/analytics.ts&#96; - Analytics utilities (create this)
+ - Landing pages in &#96;/app/&#96;
+ 
+ ## Immediate Tasks
+ 
+ ### 1. Install Meta Pixel
+ Add Meta Pixel to the site:
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;tsx
+ // In app/layout.tsx or a dedicated component
+ &lt;Script id="meta-pixel" strategy="afterInteractive"&gt;
+   {&#96;
+     !function(f,b,e,v,n,t,s)
+     {if(f.fbq)return;n=f.fbq=function(){n.callMethod?
+     n.callMethod.apply(n,arguments):n.queue.push(arguments)};
+     if(!f._fbq)f._fbq=n;n.push=n;n.loaded=!0;n.version='2.0';
+     n.queue=[];t=b.createElement(e);t.async=!0;
+     t.src=v;s=b.getElementsByTagName(e)[0];
+     s.parentNode.insertBefore(t,s)}(window, document,'script',
+     'https://connect.facebook.net/en_US/fbevents.js');
+     fbq('init', 'YOUR_PIXEL_ID');
+     fbq('track', 'PageView');
+   &#96;}
+ &lt;/Script&gt;
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ### 2. Create Analytics Utilities
+ Build &#96;/lib/analytics.ts&#96; with functions for:
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;ts
+ // Track custom events
+ export function trackEvent(eventName: string, params?: Record&lt;string, any&gt;) {
+   if (typeof window !== 'undefined' &amp;&amp; window.fbq) {
+     window.fbq('track', eventName, params);
+   }
+ }
+ 
+ // Track lead form submissions
+ export function trackLead(role: string, source: string) {
+   trackEvent('Lead', { role, source });
+ }
+ 
+ // Track email signups
+ export function trackEmailSignup(source: string) {
+   trackEvent('CompleteRegistration', { source });
+ }
+ 
+ // Track outbound clicks
+ export function trackOutboundClick(destination: string) {
+   trackEvent('OutboundClick', { destination });
+ }
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ### 3. Set Up Conversion Events
+ Configure tracking for:
+ - Page views (automatic with Pixel)
+ - Lead form submissions
+ - Email signups
+ - Outbound clicks to OTW site
+ - Outbound clicks to fund decks/overviews
+ 
+ ### 4. Create UTM Handling
+ Build utilities to:
+ - Parse UTM parameters from URLs
+ - Store UTM data in session/cookies
+ - Include UTM data in lead submissions
+ 
+ ### 5. Optimize Landing Pages
+ Ensure each landing page has:
+ - Single primary CTA
+ - Fast load time (mobile-first)
+ - Clear value proposition above fold
+ - Tracking events on key actions
+ 
+ ## Landing Pages to Optimize
+ 
+ | Page | Primary CTA | Conversion Event |
+ |------|-------------|------------------|
+ | &#96;/fund&#96; | "Partner With Us" | Lead (funder) |
+ | &#96;/projects/oakland-tech-week&#96; | "Visit OTW" | OutboundClick |
+ | &#96;/projects/code-vibes&#96; | "Apply Now" | Lead (artist/founder) |
+ | &#96;/projects/hiiiwav-fest&#96; | "Get Involved" | Lead (various) |
+ | &#96;/joint-ventures&#96; | "Become a JV" | Lead (artist) |
+ | &#96;/donate&#96; | "Donate Now" | InitiateCheckout |
+ 
+ ### 6. Ad Copy Support
+ Create a system for:
+ - Storing ad copy variants
+ - A/B testing landing page headlines
+ - Message matching between ads and landing pages
+ 
+ ## Constraints
+ - Exclude &#96;/ops&#96; from Pixel tracking
+ - All tracking must be GDPR/CCPA compliant
+ - Ad copy must be reviewed by humans before launch
+ 
+ ## Dependencies
+ - None - you can start immediately
+ 
+ ## Handoffs
+ - Ops Agent will use analytics data for reporting
+ - AI Agent may help generate ad copy variants
+ 
+ ## Reference
+ Always check &#96;/docs/website_plan.md&#96; Section 7 for marketing specifications.
